devdoc.details: A fun game contract for teaching Solidity concepts. Players must send Ether via selfdestruct or deposit, solve challenges to increase their withdrawal limits, and withdraw Ether after a lock period. The contract owner manages the whitelist. See instructions: `https://tinyurl.com/EtherVault`

addToWhitelist(address[]).details: Add multiple addresses to the whitelist.

canWithdraw(address).details: Check if the user can withdraw at the current time.

returns._0: bool True if the user can withdraw, false otherwise.

checkWhitelistStatus(address).details: Check if an address is whitelisted.

returns._0: bool True if the address is whitelisted, false otherwise.

constructor.details: Constructor sets the deployer as the owner

deposit().details: Deposit Ether to be recognized as a big spender. Only allows deposits of at least 0.01 ether.

getWithdrawalLimit(address).details: Determine the user's withdrawal limit based on their role.

returns._0: The withdrawal limit for the user.

guessMagicWord(string).details: Guess the magic word ("Solidity") to unlock higher withdrawals.

removeFromWhitelist(address[]).details: Remove multiple addresses from the whitelist.

params._users: Array of addresses to remove from the whitelist.

withdraw().details: Withdraw Ether based on the user's role after the lock period.

deploymentTime.details: Deployment timestamp and lock period (2 days)

etherSent.details: Track Ether sent and withdrawn per address
